column11: Products and features are relevant to what customer wants (8)
column18: Feedback
Well-structured submission with good role definition, relevant questions, and clear next steps, but formatting, grammar, and table readability issues reduce clarity, and no recording was provided.
Well-structured report with clear roles, follow-up questions and next steps, but it lacks a full transcript, balanced questioning, and has minor grammar and formatting issues.
Submission is generally well-organized and captures key interview insights, but question structuring and clarity could be stronger and some tables/transcript elements are only partially complete.
Submission captures a complete transcript and relevant product research but lacks clear structure, readable tables, and a thorough articulation of remaining questions and next steps.
Well-structured submission with comprehensive roles and relevant questions, but transcript quality, readability, and articulation of remaining questions need improvement.

The submission presents a clear project idea with assigned roles and a usable transcript, but lacks depth in analysis, learning points, remaining questions, and evidence of recording, while structural and grammatical quality could be improved.
Well-structured submission with clear roles and a solid question list, but lacks full transcript, readable tables, and detailed unresolved questions, and recording link is missing.
Submission shows a reasonable grasp of requirements with clear roles and pending questions, but suffers from weak grammar, incomplete transcript, and missing recording.
Good identification of roles, competitor analysis, and next steps, but organization, grammar, transcript detail, and table formatting need improvement.

Submission is reasonably structured and covers key elements, but grammar, readability of the table, and evidence of recording are weak. Good summary and next-steps, although question design and clarity could be improved.
Submission is well-structured and captures key requirements, but lacks a written transcript, has formatting issues, and contains some grammatical errors.
Submission shows solid role definition and relevant questioning but suffers from weak grammar, partial transcript, and lacks an actual recording; structure and clarity could be improved.
Well-structured submission with relevant questions and solid next steps, but lacks a real interview transcript, recording, and has only moderate depth in analysis and reflections.
Roles and basic goals are presented, but the interview lacks structure, depth, and a recording; grammar and formatting issues detract from clarity.
Submission captures main decisions and contains relevant questions but lacks a transcript, clear next-step plan, and polished grammar/formatting.
Submission identifies roles and includes some relevant questions but is poorly structured, lacks depth, and omits outstanding questions and recording.
Well-structured submission with relevant roles and a good summary, but grammar issues, lack of full transcript, and limited pending questions reduce clarity and completeness.
Submission is well-structured and covers key areas, but lacks a transcript, has formatting issues, and some sections need deeper detail and clearer grammar.
Submission is well-structured with relevant questions and clear next steps, but lacks defined roles, a transcript, and has grammar issues.
Well-structured submission with a reasonable mix of relevant questions, but the transcript is incomplete, next steps and open issues are weak, and grammar and role clarity need improvement.
Submission shows basic structure and some relevant content, but lacks depth, clear formatting, and a full transcript; several criteria only partially met.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, relevant questions and defined next steps, but lacks a full transcript, has mediocre grammar, and some tables and question flows could be clearer.
The submission is generally well-organized with clear roles, relevant questions, and a reasonable plan, but transcript detail, grammar, and formatting could be strengthened.

Submission offers a basic outline of roles, questions and feature ideas but lacks depth, coherent structure, full transcript, and clear next steps; numerous grammar issues and missing recording further weaken it.
Well-structured report with relevant content and clear role assignments, but lacks a full transcript, strong question design, and explicit next steps or remaining questions.
Comprehensive content with relevant questions and follow-up, but weak organization, limited transcript detail, and grammar issues reduce clarity and impact.
Well-structured submission with clearly assigned team roles and a functional interview script, but exhibits grammatical issues and limited depth in analysis, open questions, and future uncertainties.
Solid capture of roles and main requirements, but weak grammar, poorly formatted tables, and minimal reflection or remaining questions reduce clarity and depth.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, transcript, and relevant analysis, but grammar issues and limited depth in remaining questions and next steps reduce effectiveness.
Well-structured submission with relevant questions and solid summaries, but transcript detail and remaining questions are limited.
Submission is reasonably organized and covers roles, interview content, and next steps but lacks full transcript, structured questioning, and recording; several sections are only partially developed.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, a detailed transcript and thoughtful next steps, but grammar issues, moderate question design and readability limitations reduce clarity.
Good structure, defined roles and relevant questions, but lacks full transcript, has grammar issues and tables/transcript readability could be improved.
Report is decently structured with relevant analysis and a basic plan forward; however, lack of full transcript, missing recording, and limited clarity on remaining questions reduce completeness.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, relevant questions, and actionable next steps, though the transcript and tables are partial and some grammatical issues persist.
Submission is well-organized and captures key requirements, but lacks a full transcript, has minor grammatical issues, and tables/screenshots are not clearly included.
Submission is reasonably organized and covers key points, but grammar, question design, and transcript detail are weak, limiting clarity and depth.
Contains essential elements and recording link, but lacks transcript, has grammar issues and duplicated sections; structure and analysis are adequate but could be clearer and more detailed.
Submission is reasonably organized with relevant content and mix of question types, but transcript, tables, grammar, and clarity of learning points need improvement.
Submission is generally well-organized with clear roles and relevant content, but lacks depth in transcript, learning points, and structured questioning.
Well-organized submission with defined roles, relevant content, and a provided recording; however, grammar issues, uneven question structure, and formatting problems limit clarity and depth.
Submission is reasonably structured and addresses most required sections, but depth, clarity and completeness are moderate; tables, grammar, and question design need improvement.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, relevant questions and a working link; however, the transcript is only a summary and some learning points and unresolved questions could be deeper.
Well-organized submission with clear role allocation and relevant research, but grammar issues, limited remaining questions, and missing recording link reduce marks.

Well-structured submission with clear roles, relevant questions, and thoughtful next steps, but grammar issues, limited transcript detail, and only moderate depth in analysis and remaining questions reduce the score.
Well-structured submission with clear roles and next steps, but thin transcript and limited depth in questioning and analysis reduce overall effectiveness.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, relevant questions, and solid next steps, but lacks a real transcript, readable tables, and recording; grammar and learning points could be improved.
Well-structured submission with clear roles, learning points and next steps, but question flow and table readability could be improved.
Solid effort with comprehensive roles, relevant questions, and a provided recording, but the structure, clarity, grammar, and depth of analysis need improvement.
Well-structured submission with clear roles and relevant questions, but lacks a full transcript, detailed tables, and an explicit list of remaining questions or next steps.
Submission covers roles, open questions, competitive analysis and provides recording, but lacks transcript, clear structure and depth of insights, with several grammatical issues.
Submission covers key areas and offers a concise summary, but formatting, grammar, and depth are weak, and several rubric items are only partially satisfied.
Submission covers essential elements but lacks coherence, readable tables, and full transcript; grammar and question depth need improvement.
Submission demonstrates basic structure, role allocation, and next steps, but lacks transcript, tables, and recording, and the questions and summaries need clearer organization and depth.
Well-structured submission with relevant questions and solid summary, but grammar, clarity of learning points, open issues, and readability of the analysis table need improvement.
Submission is reasonably structured with relevant questions and role definitions, but lacks a full transcript, clear learning points, and detailed next steps.
Decent structure and relevant content, but lacks transcript, readable tables, and contains grammatical issues; next steps and summary are adequate but some criteria only partially addressed.
